edu.stmc

Class SPRT.Ternary

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stmc.SPRT.Ternary
  • Enclosing class:
    SPRT

    public static final class SPRT.Ternary
extends java.lang.Object
    SPRT for ternary simple hypothesis testing.
    • Ternary means if the algorithm terminates, there are three possibilities for its answer.
    • Simple means null and alternative hypotheses must be in the form of H0: p=p0 and H1: p=p1, respectively (for some values of 0<p0<p1<1). Note that H0: p<p0 is not a simple hypothesis.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Ternary

        public Ternary(double threshold,
               double alpha,
               double beta,
               double gamma,
               double delta)
        Construct an instance of the ternary version of SPRT
        Parameters:
        threshold - Input threshold
        alpha - Type I error probability (also known as false positive probability) is the probability of incorrectly rejecting the null hypothesis.
        beta - Type II error probability (also known as false negative probability) is the probability of incorrectly not rejecting the null hypothesis.
        gamma - The probability of returning unknown when the actual probability is at least delta away from the input threshold.
        delta - Half of the size of indifference region.
        Requires:
        0 < lb < threshold < ub < ub < 1, 0 < alpha < 0.5, 0 < beta < 0.5, 0 < gamma < 0.5

    • Method Detail

      • status

        public static GTResult.Ternary status(GTResult.Binary lb,
                                      GTResult.Binary ub)
        Parameters:
        lb - Result of lower-bound binary test
        ub - Result of upper-bound binary test
        Returns:
        GTResult.Ternary.YES, GTResult.Ternary.NO, GTResult.Ternary.UNKNOWN, or GTResult.Ternary.UNDECIDED.
        • GTResult.Ternary.YES means that the test rejected the null hypothesis (the actual probability is not smaller than the threshold in H0).
        • GTResult.Ternary.NO means that the test did not reject the null hypothesis.
        • GTResult.Ternary.UNKNOWN means that the test is finished, but could not determine an answer.
        • GTResult.Ternary.UNDECIDED means that the test is not done yet.
        Ensures:
        Let p be the actual probability. There are two two probabilistic guarantees:
        • If p <= threshold - delta then the probability of returning GTResult.Ternary.YES is at most alpha.
        • If p >= threshold + delta then the probability of returning GTResult.Ternary.NO is at most beta.
        • If threshold - delta < p < threshold + delta then the probability of returning GTResult.Ternary.UNKNOWN is at most beta.
